    <div class = "cont-DMD">
      <p>
        The most common muscular dystrophy in children is Duchenne muscular dystrophy. It's an illness that causes muscles to weaken over time, eventually affecting the entire body. It is not contagious to have Duchenne muscular dystrophy. Duchenne affects around one out of every 5,000 boys, and 20,000 kids are born with it each year throughout the world. Duchenne affects predominantly boys and affects people of all colours and cultures. Even brothers with the same mutation may experience symptoms in quite different ways. The symptoms of Duchenne are progressive, ranging from mild to severe.</p>
      
